---
import { siteMeta } from '../../../config/siteContent';
---

<div class="panel-inner">
  <div class="grid items-center gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_0.9fr]">
    <div>
      <p class="section-label" data-i18n="why.label">Why SpecLens</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-950 sm:text-3xl" data-i18n="why.title">
        Network verification tells you whether a configuration is correct. SpecLens explains why.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-600 sm:text-base" data-i18n="why.lead">
        After verification succeeds, operators still need to understand which configuration elements matter, what each one must preserve, and which local edits remain safe.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-ink-700">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">→</span> <span data-i18n="why.q1">Which configuration elements make the property hold?</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">→</span> <span data-i18n="why.q3">Which local edits are safe?</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">→</span> <span data-i18n="why.q4">Which lines or fields are irrelevant to this property?</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-ink-500">
        <span data-i18n="hero.paperVenue">Based on the ACM SIGCOMM 2026 paper</span> ·
        <em class="not-italic text-ink-700">{siteMeta.corePaper.title}</em>
      </p>
    </div>
    <figure class="surface-card overflow-hidden p-3">
      <img src="/figures/ui.png" alt="SpecLens explanation interface" class="w-full rounded-md" loading="eager" />
    </figure>
  </div>
</div>
